        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4. Syt10 Is Essential for STFP-Induced LTP of G-M Synapses\nFigure 5. IGF1 Induces Rapid Postsynaptic Potentiation of G-M Synapses Requiring IGF1-R Signaling\nFigure 6. IGF1-R Signaling Is Required by STFP-Induced LTP of G-M Synapses\n\nImportant: \"Since the Syt10 KO ablates activity-dependent IGF1 secretion (Cao et al., 2011)...\". Experimental description: \"Adult mice (age between 3 to 5 months old) with or without prior viral injections were used \"" ;
